fields.descriptive_line: Box, carved tortoiseshell, Guangzhou, China, Qing dynasty, Daoguang reign period (1821-1850), ca. 1820-1840
fields.physical_description: Tortoiseshell box, oblong shape, fitted with a lock on the outside and a tray and fittings inside, carved all over the exterior with figures and landscapes in relief.

fields.public_access_description: This box is fitted with a lock and was probably meant to serve as a jewellery box. It features an intricate and complex design that is typical of the early 19th century. To carve tortoiseshell is very similar to carving ivory, and this box was probably manufactured by the same workshop in Canton that produced carved ivory objects.
